DialogueText: Something hit your head or what?
[NC]And here I was thinking we had something special...
[pic=6]Then again, I don't mind being used.
[NSC]As long as I get to use you, too.
[NSC]Let's see what we can find out!
[RG]But I guess we're about to find out.
[R]And the other one is left in tears.
I don't know who you are.
[NS]It's high-time we get to know each other.
[S]Is this guy showing up or what?
[pic=6]But I had so much time to think about what to say...
[NSC]And now I don't know where to start.
[pic=6]I enjoyed the sound of your voice very much.
[NGD]And just can't get enough of it!
[NSC]Can you do it one more time?
[S]I guess we'll just silently stare at each other.
I guess we'll see who's got more time on their hands.
There's only few things worse than being ignored.
But after a while, it kinda grows on you.
You forget how to speak, entirely.
Guess we won't be getting along, after all.
Now go be an asshole somewhere else.
But teasing you is just way too much fun! :)
[S]I'm not really in a position to judge.
[S]So how about we make a trade?
[NSC]Would you mind doing me a favour?
[pic=6]You know my real name, don't you?
What the fuck are you on about?
[RC]So you did pay attention, after all.
[pic=6]And I guess there's something to take away from that, as well.
[pic=6]Seeing as you were kind enough to indulge me...
[NSC]I'll let you in on a little something.
I've been terribly lonely for the last year.
[pic=6]If anything, it's been a blessing in disguise.
[NSC]Certain things are better enjoyed from afar.
[pic=6]And when your entire existence revolves around a few square feet...
[NSC]You can't help but realise how terribly subjective everything is.
[pic=6]Because the only thing that really, really matters...
[NC]Though at least I get to pick my poison, right?
I know you've been leading me around.
[pic=6]You got to walk me like a dog...
[pic=28]That's what I'm telling myself, at least.
[NGD]I'm not trying to play you or anything!
[pic=6]If anything, I'm the one who's being played.
[pic=29]Just imagine how I felt when you came along.
[pic=28]How a single glimpse of you turned my whole world upside down.
[pic=6]So now that I've gotten a taste of that...
[NSC]I really don't want to let go anymore.
[NSC]Which means it's time for you to ask yourself a question.
[pic=35]Don't you dare change the fucking subject!
[pic=34]If you won't tell me what you're doing here...
[pic=14]That's a bit harsh, don't you think?
[pic=6]And not something you should say to a visitor.
[S]Are you kidding me with that question?
[NSC]I guess there's only one way to find out.
[S]If you're going to shoot me again-
[SC]Do you seriously think you'll get any sympathy from me...
[S]Just because there's a few bruises on your neck?
But I really, really can't find it in me to give a shit about you and your past.
[SC]You wanted to know how I got in, right?
And today, I almost killed myself.
[NSC]How does it compare to the real thing?
[SC]That's a really nice fantasy you got going there.
Because I'm really just rambling to myself.
[NC]The kind of thing people do after months of isolation.
[pic=12]I'm sure it had to be pretty hard on you.
[pic=11]What was it like, not seeing them again for so long?
[NSC]I don't think you understand how serious this really is.
[S]Then how about you get to the fucking point?
I don't know what kind of bullshit you're up to, this time.
[SC]And I'd rather not bleed to death.
I barely grazed your leg, if anything.
[pic=34]I guess this is the part where you want me to say "thanks"?
[pic=13]This is the part where you should admit it already, you dumb fuck!
[S]Because you're very good at getting a response.
Andreos is your colleague, isn't he?
He knew about it from you, didn't he?
You can spell a colour, right?
We should both be seeing the same thing.
But it's been a long time coming.
[NSC]At least I made it through in one p-
[SC]If you weren't standing in front of me...
You really want to do this?
[NSC]I know it's rough on you, too.
[NSC]Me, and the person you used to be.
[S]You might want to close your eyes.
[NSC]But I'm perfectly fine the way I am.
But you never told your boss about it...
[S]You know what happens to greedy people, right?
You should really learn how to take a win.
[NC]Look. \ It's great that you're telling me things I already know.
Really! \ I could do this all day.
In some way, we're blessed to forget.
[NSC]Because I know how much it hurts.
[NC]I'm glad we're on the same page.
Because we don't have a lot of time.
[RGC]I bet there's a lot of demand for you, these days.
[NG]Or do you really have no fucking clue?
[R]I can't even tell what date it is, anymore.
Atlas was with you at Icarus' place.
[S]You told your doctor you were alone.
[RC]You want me to write it down?
Not like anyone believes you, anyway.
I just wanted to clear that up.
You've got something on your mind?
[S]But we can't leave it like that.
[NSC]Maybe I should beat you to a pulp...
That would be boring,\,\, wouldn't it?\n
[SC]Guess I'll have to hold this conversation by myself, hm?
[NC]I just thought the two of us should talk...
What do you want to talk about?
Is there nothing you want to say?
But I can't help if I don't know what your problem is.
[SC]You want to know what my problem is?
[SC]If this is what Trachi will be like.
[S]We might as well call it off.
[SP]We're supposed to work together, you fucking idiot!
[SC]But I've got no clue where you're going with this.
[NC]Isn't that what I'm doing, right now?
And we're packing one of them.
We'll take him out first thing once we're in.
You think that's a good idea?
But I know there'll be eyes on us.
There's a remark about one of <color=#811e1e>A<color=#FFFFFF>mryn's generals.
Do you know where he's staying?

Sequence: SendMessage(Close, , Subtitle Panel);\nrequired Music(War, FadeOut, 5, false);\nContinue()@3;

DialogueText: [SC]Can this guy be on time, just once?
[NPC]Beats pacing around in circles, I guess.
[NS]I bet he won't show up for another hour or so.
You know he's gonna arrive the exact moment-
[SPC]If we're lucky, it'll teach him a thing or two about punctuality.
[S]Hardly get a word out of him, lately.
[S]Don't you guys think it's better to wait until he's here?
[NSC]Since when do you care about formalities?
[SC]He'll want to hear every little detail.
[SPC]Which means I'll have to listen to it, too.
[NSC]Let's talk about something you don't want him to hear.
[R]You can do much better than that!
[SC]Not having this conversation, for a start.
[NSC]I heard a little story, you know.
[S]You might as well tell the story to that cupboard, over there.
[S]When was the last time you saw her?
[S]We should kill her the moment she gets here.
But it's our best one, too.
[S]Don't tell me he's roping you in..
[NSC]But it's the only reasonable option here.
[RC]If anything, I'm the one to blame.
[S]There’s no telling if Gany even gets here in one piece!
Atlas said he'll keep him safe.
[S]Because two EnTARDs can't be worse than one, right?
Do you really want to know?
[S]I didn’t mind helping you set this up.
[SC]But if you really want us to throw ourselves into the fire…
[S]We need to know what's going on.
[RC]Just keep in mind she'll come for you.
[NC]Tomorrow afternoon, three people will arrive in <color=#811e1e>T<color=#FFFFFF>rachi.
As you know, Hyperion has his eyes both on me and Eury.
And dead people can’t defend themselves very well.
How does he know we're here, in the first place?
[S]I won't shoot you in the head, even though I should.
But you don't need to do this for him.
And how much you want to set it free.
And Atlas, too, a few weeks after that.
Though hopefully, we'll have everyone on our side come the 28th.
Planting both herself and Ganymede in <color=#811e1e>I<color=#FFFFFF>onia.
[NC]Making sure that there’s no more operations like these.
And once we’re standing on our own feet…
But what exactly makes you sure he won’t fuck us over?
[S]And don’t give me the revenge bullshit again…
[NC]According to our files, Atlas' parents died between 03 and 05.
[NC]According to him, his father was shot dead in 04.
Leaving his mother as his last remaining relative.
She’s a lovely lady, very endearing.
[NC]If Atlas isn't with us by the 28th...
If push comes to shove, I'll confront him.
[NC]And if he still wants to walk the line…
[NC]You see, we’re all tied up in this, in some way.
Everyone but the two of you.
[NC]For me, my brother and Eury here…
[NC]Then again, if I’m to be brutally honest…
[pic=10]You know this is our home, right?
[SC]Then why in god's name are you setting it on fire?
[NC]It's the only way to save it.
[NC]Me and Eury were sent here for a reason.
[SC]Solka would've marched his people to the parliament.
[R]And we'd all be speaking Greek, again.
I never told Solka about his orders.
And I didn't want you to become traitors, too.
[RC]I care too much about this city, you see.
[NC]I let myself get caught by Eury.
And told her the entire truth.
[NC]The role I played in her sister's death.
To me committing acts of treason.
You can trust him as much as you can trust me.
I died a long time ago.
And there's no way to ever bring her back.
But the thing she fought against...
Imagine my rage, multiplied a thousandfold.
[NC]The colour's a bit washed out, though.
You don't like it that way?
[pic=6]Is this what Eury had to put up with all these years?
[NC]For her sake, I hope your brother makes it out alive.
[pic=6]I'm free to spend my time sulking about the past again.
I wish I could see it that way, too.
Was it your idea or his?
[SC]I've met a lot of crazy people in my time...
[S]But your brother takes the fucking cake.
[NC]And considering what Daph did to him...
I bet he's having the time of his life right now.
How long do you think we got?
Couple of months at least, he said.
[NC]Though I'm more worried about the situation right here.
[NSC]And eventually, people wil remember that they need to eat.
But they can't help us if <color=#811e1e>A<color=#FFFFFF>mryn's not letting them through.
They want both him and Tanner.
Unless you want me to activate her already?
If anything, we'd waste our only bullet on a warning shot.
Just throwing ideas into the mix.
[NC]Let's go and have a chat with the ambassador.
Or she'd kill you on the spot.
I promised that I'd keep you safe.
[S]There's no fucking way he'd go along with that!
[NC]He told me something else, as well.
In case you wouldn't believe me.
[NC]You killed another kid, when you were six.
[S]Did you tell her about that, too?
[SC]For someone who’s that keen on taking responsibility…
[NC]Keeping you busy until she gets here.
You're pointing a gun at one of your associates.
[NC]So I'd hurry up, if I were you.
But my life's on the line here, too.
Though I guess we're about to find out.
Glad we're thinking the same thing.
[NC]I thought I should let you know.
[NC]Next time you pull a gun on me...
[S]Is that your idea of working together?
Would you mind if we went back to the first night?
Though I think I’ve already told you everything.
You said you've followed one of <color=#811e1e>A<color=#FFFFFF>mryn’s "mules".
That’s when you heard the gunshot?
Me and everybody else in the area.
What did you make of it?
I figured someone at the checkpoint flipped.
But that’s not what really happened, right?
What do you mean by that?
[NC]The guy storming the barricade was a smokescreen.
So Nestville could break one of their people out.
[S]I was pretty clueless at that point.
Did you come across anything unusual?
So you went back to the safehouse?
[NC]Or rather, I realised what had been going on.
[pic=1]We made the deal, the day before.
[NC]But the legwork went to someone else.
That's why you went to his apartment?
Why do you think he told you?
I hadn’t slept the day before we arrived.
But weren’t you supplied with alpha-methylphenethylamine?
It says here you were issued a bottle with twenty pills.
Is that how you call it?
They were all gone by that point.
You went through the entire bottle in a couple of days?
I had them when we entered <color=#811e1e>T<color=#FFFFFF>rachi.
[NC]But when I woke up, they were gone.
Probably lost them when I got pushed into the sewers.
[NC]Or maybe a certain someone took them from me.
How much did you sleep in total during those three days?
[NC]I was able to catch up a bit on the 28th.
[SC]Before I got all my fingers broken.
[S]And dragged to this place like I was a fucking traitor.
Do you remember any particular dreams?
Would you mind if I showed you something?
[S]This better not be about that ATOPIA stuff again-
Have you ever seen anything like it before?
[NC]Have you ever felt as if you weren't there?
[R]Do you want to be somewhere else?
Now think about a painful memory.
At the risk of making that mistake again?
[NP]How long has this been going on?
[S]I want to fix it either way!
[RPC]You love me because I want to put things right.
[NC]If that's how you want to put it.
[RP]And I love you because you won't let me.
[NC]As long as we don't make it a habit.
[NSC]I might be off for a couple of weeks anyway.
[NSC]Something about a city and a dam.
[NS]If you want to talk some more.
Would you do the stupid thing again?
Even it if erased your former self?
The one that made a mistake.
That's why I'm in love with you.
[NC]Is that why I love you, too?
And I'm assuming he was also present that night.
According to him, <color=#811e1e>a<color=#FFFFFF>rteria was more important.
[NC]It’s a load of horse crap, alright.
But I’m sure we’ll get to the bottom of it.
What did Icarus tell you, exactly?
You think he was hiding something?
[NC]I worked him like I’ve never worked anyone before.
If there wasn’t something big going on, he would’ve folded.
What do you make of it?
I think they were all in on it.
That goes for all of us.
[S]But I guess some people can't let go.
If you want me to go ba-
[NC]I understand your desire to make it right.
But you know fully well that’s not going to happen.
We’ll have more than enough work on our hands.
[NC]I pushed the hearing to three days from now.
That should give us ample time to set your story straight.
I trust you understand who’s to be held responsible?
You want to lay it on Fero?
If he kept his flock in check, none of this would’ve happened.
Before Atlas met that Lorna girl.
You said there's reason to assume he was present during Icarus' death.
[NC]Along with the fact that he shot you.
Just when you were about to apprehend Orpheus and Eurydice.
[NC]His motivations remain unclear, to this date.
But we assume a romantical relationship with Eurydice to be the primary cause.
There's marks all over his neck.
Can you hold his head for me?
[SC]But both of us know it's too late for him.
But it's written all over your face.
[NGD]But it's written all over your face!
Why be afraid of it, in the first place?
[NGD]But it's written all over your face!
[pic=6]If you think you can flatter your way out of this-
I guess the memory's still fresh.
[NSC]I guess I'm the same as you.
[NSC]I guess I'm the same as you.
[S]And you just left him like that?
And will be, until he either slowly withers away...
Because I'm having this conversation, instead.
Guess it hurts seeing someone hurting like that.
Either way, it's your call now.
[NC]There's got to be a better way.
But I'd rather not stand around thinking about it.
[NC]And besides, he's not the person you're looking for.
It would make for a rather awkward conversation.
[NSD]Don't make me wait too long, darling.
[NS]Would you mind getting those from the pantry?
[RS]Brunch should be ready in a minute.
[R]I'm terribly sorry, but I just remembered that I urgently need to be somewhere.
[NC]Wish it could wait, but there's nothing I can do, I'm afraid.
[R]I feel very embarrassed putting you to work like that and not even giving something in return.
[RS]How about you take some of that stew with you?
[NS]We prepared lunch for four people, after all!
[RS]I think Drenem was discussing a few things with someone, upstairs.
[R]I tried not to listen too attentively, since it's none of my business.
[S]Though Drenem sounded like he got quite worked up.
[RC]He really should take it easy, sometimes.
[RS]In any case, I think I heard her leave, just now.
[NSD]So I guess it's up to you to take her share.
[NSD]And thank you for helping me out, as well.
[SS]Please give my best regards to Mr. Hendrick as well.
[NGD]I'll make sure to invite the two of you over!
[NSD]And please let me know how the stew was.
[NSD]Hope you have a nice afternoon, Terry!
[NC]And here I was thinking we had something special...
[pic=6]Then again, I don't mind being used.
[NSC]As long as I get to use you, too.
[NSC]Let's see what we can find out!
[R]And the other one is left in tears.
[S]Then I guess I'll have to kill you again.
What if you don't get back up?
[SC]Why don't you point it out for me?
[NSC]I know a devil when I see one.
[S]You ought to be better than that!
[S]Do you want to be a monster too?
[SC]If that's what you think of me.
You won't have to worry about that, anymore.
[NP]I guess I'm not as clever as I thought.
To tell me what the fuck's going on.
[NSC]Is that why you wanted a fight?
[NC]You said the rain brought you back to life?
[NC]You said the rain brought you back to life?
[S]We gotta get out of this mess!
My life's at stake, you dolt.
[S]Would you rather spend your time with him?
[S]And you can't make me either, by the looks of it.
[S]The thing you've been doing the entire time.
[NS]I had a lot of time to think.
Let's hope a break sorts him out.
[NSC]I think I owe you a bit of gratitude.
[S]I just got an itch to kill you again.
[S]What the fuck's that supposed to mean?
I don't want to stay like this.
You need to kill me, again.
This is no way to live.
[pic=33]And besides, I'd rather not stay around for your honeymoon.
[pic=32]I wouldn't want to impose on your honeymoon.
[S]I was thinking if I should ask.
What the fuck's that supposed to mean?
[pic=6]Or maybe, we should thank THEM instead.

DialogueText: [NSC]You've kept some for yourself, didn't you?
[pic=32]And still plenty left in the tank.
[NC]You told me to go all out.
[pic=6]To come back a little stronger each time.
[pic=6]Could be the building block of a human being.
[SC]I said the rain is only half the story.
[NC]To make us walk and talk and dream..
We need some form of light.
We need some form of light.
[pic=6]Something you should be familiar with by now.
[S]Don't tell me you've spent it all.
[pic=6]It has a drive to stay alive.
[pic=6]I have a reason to stay alive.
Maybe there's a god after all.
[S]I can only tell you what I see.
[S]Starting with everything he said to you.
[S]Tell me what he told about Lorna.
[RG]Do I really need to spell it out for you?
And you want me to save it?
[SC]Don't make me beat you up again.
[NSC]If you want to waste your energy on me.
[S]I don't see a lot of alternatives.
[SC]Who taught you how to read it?
[S]I'll do it again if I have to.
How much more do you need?
[N]I'd rather you get to the point.
[NC]I guess you want something from me.
[NSC]You know the world's a bit unhinged, lately.
[NS]Would you like to make it right?
[S]I'm not the one who killed him.
Why wasn't your brother in Trachi?
Can you do it or not?
You know I'd go through hell for her.
[NS]You know what's written in the RAIN?
[S]Did I say I'd make it easy?
We'll take it step by step.
[NS]You don't want to turn your back on her.
[NSC]They say your heart's in the right place, Lorna.
[NC]And here I thought I've seen it all.
[NGD]I was hoping I could shut you down.
[NP]You're making it sound like I'm the cause.
[NC]I told you not to mess with RAIN.
We'll find a way to unmake it.
[S]You've got to be better than that.
[NS]Would you want to be a hero?
[S]Who do you think rebuilt that place?
Is that why Ariadne wanted to die?
These things are made of RAIN?
Off the grid, so to speak!
What happens to garbage if no one picks up?
Leave it to you to be negative.
You don't need to see them.
[NC]Just say what you want to say.
IF the world is made of rain.
Why don't you try and ask?
Now that you got your brother inside of y-
[S]I got a score to settle, anyway.
Do you know why you're here?
[2]And here I was thinking we had something special...
[6]Then again, I don't mind being used.
[5]As long as I get to use you, too.
[5]Let's see what we can find out!
[7]And the other one is left in tears.
I'm saying even if she's mad...
You shouldn't feel bad about it.
Cleo, have you met our neighbours?
Would you mind seeing what she's up to?
[NSC]Life is full of surprises, isn't it?
[NS]I'm just relieved you like it here.
[RC]We had to run because of me.
It just feels like I should.
[R]You told me to forget my name!
You said it to me yesterday!
You're feeling guilty because of me.
I told myself I was protecting you.
[NC]When I was just afraid let you go.
That's no reason to feel bad about yourself!
Where people like us can forgive ourselves.
But it's time for me to grow up.
Do we really need another world for that?
[NSC]I'm glad you see it that way.
You need to listen to me.
You need to listen to me.
[3]Then tell me what the fuck is going on!
[3]Because it's the only thing you ever do!
[3]Just tell me the what's going on!
Do you really want to know?
[6]I should have said so a long time ago.
[2]I'm just trying to make you understand.
[2]I'm just trying to make you understand.
[2]Since you've already got it figured out.
So I'll put it into words you understand.
Everything you ever knew is gone.
There is no truth, only life and death.
This is as real as it gets.
[NC]Keep your feet to the ground, Lorna.
Because I won't hold your hand anymore.
[N]Keep your feet on the ground, okay?
But I'm exactly where I was.
[7]You're not supposed to call me that.
You said it to me yesterday!
But you do you remember that I left?
[NC]It would be rude to refuse, right?
[NS]Just give me a second, I'll set the table.
[NS]Did you have a look at your room?
You planning to go in there?
[NSC]Is that gonna take all day or?
Then I guess you'll just have to wait.
I'll need to see some papers first.
Let me know if you find it.
Why don't you go with her?
He'll be the one bothering you.
I don't know if it's any help...
But I heard a couple of people talking in the pub.
You want to check it out?
I'll stick around for a couple of hours.
Let me know if I can help.
[NC]I don't want to be a bother.
You've got an ID or something?
I thought I had my service card with me.
[NC]Not much use if I can't prove it, though.
Wish I could make an exception.
Unless you're the one making them.
Either way, let me know if you find your card.
Wait. Are you with that Anton guy?
Yeah. He had a card like this one.
Unless someone threw him out of a window.
[NGD]He's a real piece of work, isn't he?
If he's causing trouble in there-
Don't let me keep you, then.
Wait. Are you with that Anton guy?
Can I leave him in your hands?
Do you have an ID or something?
You still got your service card?
Well, let me know when you dig it up.
I don't know if it's any help...
But there's rumors going 'round in the pub.
You want to check it out?
I'll stick around for a couple of hours.
Let me know if I can help.
[NC]And here I was thinking we had something special...
[pic=6]Then again, I don't mind being used.
[NSC]As long as I get to use you, too.
[NSC]Let's see what we can find out!
[R]And the other one is left in tears.
[NS]You really think that's going to work?
[RGD]But I really can't take it anymore!
Did you have another sightseeing trip or what?
[NC]I knew there was something off about you.
There is no need for this.
What do you mean by that?
I know you've been in contact with him.
That was a long time ago.
And I told the service about that when I crossed over.
Did you know he was the one who tipped us off about Glundon?
And you still took the bait.
Or not on our side, after all.
The secretary saw you leave the building last night.
Atlas, who had meanwhile briefly been to the safehouse, leaves around ten minutes later.
And the next morning, one of our most valuable assetts is found drifting in the sewers.
Now, I don't have any proof, nor do I know what exactly happened...
But you've got to admit that this doesn't put you in a good light.
What where you doing yesterday when you went out?
I'm sure you've got it all figured out, by now.
[N]The prefecture is in Sigmund Plaza, just south of Anderson Park.
[NGD]The past is the past, after all.
[NS]I met a guy named Theo, though.
[NS]It's so nice of you to help us out!
[NS]Let's hope you get some good material.
[NS]Besides, it's very convenient for me too.
I've been meaning to ask around.
[NGD]He said he wanted to talk to you.
[NS]And I'd love to return the favor.
[NSC]Please, it's the least I can do.
